A naive approach. Life is conflict. You may resolve it with words, or with might.
Hence your bearded visitor. Even the githyanki have heard tell of Elminster, the Sage of Shadowdale, you know. Some of his works have been translated to tir'su.
I am a living example of the tadpole's benefits. I've never felt more powerful.
You would do well not to squander it; a githyanki's goodwill is even rarer than a Sharran of integrity.
That doesn't mean his every word carries wisdom, however.
Did you hear? I don't have eyes for Astarion, only for you.
Come. We must locate a crèche. Observe everything. Assume nothing.
Countless scholars roam the Astral Sea and beyond - observing the ways of our lessers, exploring planes so distant, order turns to chaos and cold fires rage.
Your bones will change form. Your jaw will split to allow room for four great tentacles.
My suggestion: attack with purpose, and savour your kills. And if the urge proves too much, well, I'm sure we can find you a goblin or two to carve up.
If it was offered in good faith, then I will offer mine in return.
Crèche Y'llek is destroyed. I doubt there were survivors.
Perhaps you... no, that's absurd.

EditorData.NodeContext: Starting to 'Perhaps you are right, and changes her mind.

Text.Value: I was trained on Crèche K'liir among the Tears of Selûne.
What do you think of it, Shadowheart?
Since I was old enough to hold a blade, I've dreamt of wielding a silver sword.

EditorData.NodeContext: Thrilled about having retrieved a silver sword

Text.Value: I've decided to pursue a relationship with Karlach. I thought you should know.
Not books, but slates. Wisdom so profound it is etched into stone. Truth as perfect as the Queen who decreed it.
Raphael's offer was quite extraordinary.

EditorData.logicalname: After speaking to Raphael in SC without making a deal, before speaking to Voss

Text.Value: You said you were going to share your bunk with Shadowheart.
We've retrieved a silver sword, the sort worthy of a gith warrior.

EditorData.logicalname: Voss didn't give sword - Didn't talk about silver sword earlier

Text.Value: It is done.
Voss seemed to think Vlaakith is a tyrant.
Come on now. Are they really that bad?
Go to camp. I'll fetch you when the time is right.
We should talk about Vlaakith's visit to camp.
Let's change the subject.
Perhaps. 'Absolute' may be a mere pseudonym behind which this master hides.
Are you sure that's the best course of action?
His contact in Baldur's Gate holds the means of releasing the one in the Prism, the means of the Githyanki Empire's destruction.
*Lae'zel hardly thinks highly of you. The truth could further damage your alliance.*
Who does the laying? I'm curious about the logistics.
That sounds awful. How are you so calm?
Then we speak the Rite of Ascension, and a red dragon comes to fly us to Vlaakith in Tu'narath, City of Death.
Otherwise, it festers. It becomes a parasite of its own. Ignore it at your peril.
Elders and collectives abide by their own tenets. It would require a powerful Creed to unite them.
Depraved or not, you are no good to our queen dead. You need these talents.
Depraved or not, you are no good to your queen dead. You need these talents.
My choices seem simple enough. One: Slay you and be done with it. Two: Go my own way. Three: Keep you well-fed with powerful magic.
Yes - best to keep quiet, lest any drivel leak from your lips.
I've had these urges. I want to kill. I want blood.
Tell Lae'zel about what happened inside the artefact.

EditorData.logicalname: Wasn't present in Astral plane and return to creche

Text.Value: Thinking of that worm inside me... it's driving me mad.
An elder brain. It lives without body, without armour, save the brine pool it inhabits.
Actually, I'd rather you stay in my party.
No matter. I do not intend to stay long in this place.
'Better' is an opinion. But mine is certainly more economical.
Perhaps, if I am in need of relief. Until then, I'll enjoy watching you squirm from the anticipation of it.
The goddess of secrets? How telling.
The pupils themselves culled the weak from their ranks.
I need more assurance than an old githyanki metaphor.
I suggest you turn your eye of judgement to her.
Of course you haven't. They would have cut you from navel to neck.
Have you thought about making use of the tadpole's power?
Yes. He's made a very tempting offer.
Many a good warrior savours the scent of blood in the air. There's no shame in a capricious murder now and again.
The queen assigns when and where they must lay, and how many eggs they must bear.
Stay in camp. I'll fetch you when the time is right.
I find it unbearable that Shadowheart possesses a gith relic.
Vlaakith promised to make you Baht t'Vlaakith. An incredible honour.
If we must bear the tadpoles' burdens, we should also avail ourselves of their power.
I've lingering doubts. Trusting a Sharran disciple goes against everything I know.
I will not be bearing the burden of the half-elf's deceit.
Yes. In great detail. It starts with a fever and memory loss.
Fever dreams born of the parasite. They should be ignored.
Every githyanki, and every red dragon, shall know me by the name.
Not since Vlaakith-One has a Baht t'Vlaakith been anointed.
It is over, where I am concerned.
You hide in the Dark Lady's shadows, threading lies and mysteries out of her decaying weave.
I'm certain. I'll find you in camp when I need you.
No. No. I will not become more ghaik than the damned parasite in my skull has already made me.
... yet we still collect more. Infinities upon infinities.
Is it me, or have you been looking at me differently?
Many would nigh lose their minds just to near one. Even... well. Most would, and have.

EditorData.NodeContext: She catches herself almost saying "Even me" and changes to "Even ... well."

Text.Value: Better to be scaled than noseless and covered in spots.
On to other matters.
Yes, for now.
'Better' is an opinion. I much prefer githyanki aesthetic to 'undersized wyrm'.
I'd like to talk about Orpheus.
The githyanki are only as powerful as their weakest warrior. Jhe'quith dvenzir - the termination of the frail - strengthens us.

EditorData.NodeContext: je-QUITH deh-VEN-zear - The systematic removal of the weak

Text.Value: A possibility. Yet it would require a powerful Creed to unite the Elders.
Yet you were already mighty. And you would have been mightier still if you'd defied him and your 'urges'.
Leave.
We've yet to attend to your needs at a githyanki crèche. Is this a bother?

EditorData.logicalname: Progressed in Act2 without doing Creche

Text.Value: Nor have I. They come to the Material Plane just long enough to pass their eggs.
Let's.
The Absolute is this 'master'. I'm sure of it.
A loathsome fate, and one I intend to avoid.
That's not going to happen. We will find a cure.
Leave.
Entirely. I was as devoted to my studies as I was to my training.
Yet I do not recommend Shadowheart seek it again.
It's not like that, Lae'zel. Accept the Astral-Touched Tadpole's power. You'll be unstoppable.

Synopsis: All questions available to the player when speaking to LZ directly
